(22359, 283, '2012-07-17 15:43:40', '2012-07-17 21:43:40', '<p><strong>Rick Walton</strong> is the author of more than thirty books for children, including So Many Bunnies: A Bedtime ABC and Counting Book and What to Do When a Bug Climbs in Your Mouth and Other Poems to Drive You Buggy. His most recent book is, “Much Ado About Mormons”. This landmark volume explores nineteenth-, twentieth-, and twenty-firstcentury Mormon society through the perspectives of journalists, novelists, travel writers, presidents, and other well-known public figures, including such varied people as Susan B. Anthony, Buffalo Bill Cody, Mark Twain, Leo Tolstoy, Vincent Price, Will Rogers, Angela Lansbury, Walter Cronkite, Margaret Thatcher, President John F. Kennedy, and dozens more.When he is not writing, he likes to read, travel, and play the guitar. Rick lives in Provo, Utah, with his wife, Ann, and their four children.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Kirk Shaw</strong> is senior editor for Covenant Communications. He has also done work for Boston publisher David R. Godine, Northwestern University Press, and the scientific journal Western North American Naturalist, among other clients. During his career, he has produced and edited fiction (in many genres), memoirs, historical, poetry, plays, art, gardening, gift, technical, scientific, creative nonfiction, and doctrinal books. He enjoys writing short stories and especially relishes reading speculative fiction, historical novels, New England poetry, young adult, postapocalyptic, and dystopia novels. He is looking for good suspense, historical, romance, adventure, and other fiction and is also looking for good gift book and inspirational/doctrinal nonfiction that would suit an LDS audience.</p>', 'Rick Walton &amp; Kirk Shaw', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rick-walton-kirk-shaw', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:22:13', '2014-05-28 07:22:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22359', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22369, 283, '2012-07-17 15:43:54', '2012-07-17 21:43:54', 'Troy Hinckley is a seasoned veteran of the film industry and has worked on many family and LDS-oriented films as a sound editor. He has also worked as a producer and writer and as an owner of Out of Time Productions and East Idaho Films. Troy has taught audio production at BYU-Idaho and currently teaches advanced audio production at Full Sail University in Florida.', 'Troy Hinckley', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'troy-hinckley', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:22:12', '2014-05-28 07:22:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22369', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22373, 283, '2012-07-17 15:44:08', '2012-07-17 21:44:08', 'As a wife, mother, licensed therapist, business owner, and award-winning singer-songwriter, Julie de Azevedo Hanks understands the juggling act women face these days. She also knows what women want—and need—in order to keep all those balls in the air.', 'Julie de Azevedo Hanks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'julie-de-azevedo-hanks', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:22:12', '2014-05-28 07:22:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22373', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22379, 283, '2012-07-17 15:44:22', '2012-07-17 21:44:22', 'Heber Longhurst is a Senior Equity Research Associate Analyst for Citibank. He co-authors sell-side research on  homebuilding, infrastructure, construction materials and commercial real estate companies in Mexico and Brazil. He also supervises two research assistants in Mexico and Brazil as well as communicating investment recommendations and consultations for international institutional investors.', 'Heber Longhurst', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'heber-longhurst', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:21:47', '2014-05-28 07:21:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22379', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22385, 283, '2012-07-17 15:44:37', '2012-07-17 21:44:37', 'Wayne Klein is a financial fraud expert and founder of Klein &amp; Associates, PLLC. As a court-appointed attorney receiver, Klein takes over companies that have been operating Ponzi schemes or other investment frauds.  He reconstructs their financial transactions, files lawsuits to recover monies paid improperly to insiders, sells assets, and distributes the recovered funds back to the victims.  One of the cases for which he is acting as Receiver is the Trigon case in Idaho Falls, Idaho, where $68 million was taken in a Ponzi scheme.', 'Wayne Klein', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'wayne-klein', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:21:46', '2014-05-28 07:21:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22385', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22387, 283, '2012-07-17 15:44:56', '2012-07-17 21:44:56', 'Shane Snow is the Founder of Brave Media LLC and Cofounder of the crowd-sourcing and publishing startup, Contently Inc.  Shane graduated from BYU-Idaho with a Bachelor’s degree in Business Management and went on to receive his Master’s degree in Journalism and Digital Media from Columbia University.For the last five years Shane has been running his own design business, Brave Media, while also working on several projects including two successful website businesses.  He has pursued several freelance journalism opportunities and is a contributing writer for Mashable, Gizmodo, Fast Company, The Huffington Post and Wired.', 'Shane Snow', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'shane-snow', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:21:46', '2014-05-28 07:21:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22387', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22390, 283, '2012-07-17 15:45:15', '2012-07-17 21:45:15', 'Les Pico is the Executive Director of Player Development and Legal for the Minnesota Vikings. He is directly involved with personal welfare and legal issues that arise concerning players, coaches and staff.  Other areas of expertise and responsibilities included in his career include implementing player programs to assist with continuing education, family assistance and career internships.  He assists the personnel staff by evaluating and interviewing players at the NFL Combine and assists in evaluations during pro free agency. Les is involved with the administration of the annual rookie symposium that is attended by all NFL drafted rookies.', 'Les Pico', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'les-pico', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:21:46', '2014-05-28 07:21:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22390', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22412, 283, '2012-07-17 15:45:51', '2012-07-17 21:45:51', 'Cherie Call was born and raised in Mesa, Arizona and has been writing music since her early teens. She has released seven full length albums of her original songs. Her latest album, “Grace”, was released in October of 2009. Some highlights of Cherie’s performing life include playing “in the round” at Nashville’s famous Bluebird Cafe, being a finalist in the prestigious Kerrville Newfolk songwriting competition, and opening for bluegrass legend Tim O’Brien at the University of Utah. Cherie’s songs have been included on several albums produced for the LDS Especially for Youth summer programs, and also on the soundtracks to many independent films, including God’s Army, Charly, and the Banff Award winning film, “True Fans”.  Cherie currently lives in Utah with her husband and two daughters.', 'Cheri Call', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cheri-call-2', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:21:30', '2014-05-28 07:21:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22412', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22414, 283, '2012-07-17 15:46:21', '2012-07-17 21:46:21', 'Jana Evans is currently a Human Resource Generalist for Merit Medical in the Salt Lake City, Utah area, which manufactures medical devices all over the globe. After graduating from college, Sister Evans began her career in Human Resources. She started in Technical Recruiting and eventually worked her way to where she is now, an HR Business Generalist. Sister Evans is a member of the Society of Human Resource Management (SHRM) and has received her Professional in Human Resources (PHR) certification. Sister Evans served a mission in South Dakota and is currently serving as the Fellowshipping Activities Co-Chair in a Mid-Singles Branch as well as a pianist for the Spanish Branch Primary in her stake.', 'Janna Evans', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'janna-evans', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:21:30', '2014-05-28 07:21:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22414', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22416, 283, '2012-07-17 15:46:34', '2012-07-17 21:46:34', '“Our Best Bites” food bloggers, co-authors of Our Best Bites: Mormon Moms in the Kitchen, a cookbook published through Deseret Book (Shadow Mountain); Winners of Better Homes and Gardens Blogger Cook-Off.\r\n\r\n“We’re just two girls who love to cook! We’re also both wives and mothers balancing home management, part-time work, church and community involvement, and a myriad of other things. So we’re probably just like you! We want to show you that cooking at home can be a delicious, fun, and easy way to express yourself and to care for your families and friends.”', 'Kate Jones and Sarah Wells', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kate-jones-and-sarah-wells', '', '', '2014-05-28 01:21:29', '2014-05-28 07:21:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22416', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
